TestReportWritesJunitXml
/ Runs a passing fixture via test.run, then test.report with format='junit'.
/ Proves: (1) format routes through the junit branch, (2) reportPath points
/ at junit.xml, (3) the file actually got written on disk. Uses the absolute
/ reportPath so file.exists doesn't hit goal-relative path resolution.
- test.discover tests in '_fixtures_pass', pattern='*.fixture.goal', recursive, write to %tests%
- test.run tests %tests%, write to %results%
- test.report results %results%, format='junit', write to %report%
- assert %report.format% equals 'junit'
- assert %report.summaryPass% equals 1
- file.exists %report.reportPath%, write to %exists%
- assert %exists% is true
